Bachelor of Nursing Courses in Australia: Courses, Universities, Scholarship

  • 1284 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Mar 27,2023 02:00 PM IST

Study Bachelor of Nursing Courses in Australia with guidance from Canam | Learn about Bachelor of nursing requirements, cheapest nursing courses, scholarships options, the cost of studying bachelor and nursing colleges in Australia and get answers to your important queries.

Australia is one of the top study-abroad destinations. Students from all over the world come to study Nursing in Australia and grab the opportunity to work as hospital workers, health administrators, mental health workers, midwives, and registered nurses. Here are some reasons why you should pursue a Bachelor of Nursing in Australia:
 
•As per QS World University Rankings 2023 Australia has some of the top-ranked universities in the world, and the education credentials you gain from these institutions are highly respected worldwide.
•You get to learn about the basics of nursing with intensive theoretical and practical knowledge and be able to deliver best of the healthcare services with your learned knowledge.
•Universities in Australia have a very high employment rate, which is above 90% for the graduates of Bachelor of Nursing.
•Among the top 10 most in-demand jobs in Australia, Nursing Jobs are among them, so you won't have to worry much after completing your degree to get a job.
•Australia's very low unemployment rate in 2023 and the rising demand for Nurses make a Bachelor of Nursing in Australia one of the best options.

Bachelor of Nursing in Australia: Specializations and Syllabus

Bachelor of nursing in Australia is generally offered full-time, and the students of nursing are required to study the following subjects such as:

•Community and Primary Health Care
•Nursing and Older People
•Chronic Disease and Disability
•Biology of Human Disease
•Health Assessment and Clinical Nursing
•Mental Health Nursing
•Nursing in Complex Settings (Perioperative)
•Cancer Care and Palliative Care Nursing
•Pharmacology for Nursing

Bachelor of Nursing in Australia: Admissions

Bachelor of Nursing in Australia has trimester patterns and usually starts in February. If students plan to apply before, their applications are accepted on a rolling basis until the program begins. To get admission in the program, students must have an excellent academic record, proof of English language proficiency and the potential to redefine the healthcare services.

Bachelor of Nursing Requirements in Australia

•If students are planning to pursue Nursing in Australia, they must have a minimum score of 75% in their Grade 12 or equivalent to studying in Australia.
•English language proficiency through tests like IELTS, TOEFL, etc.
•Students should meet the requirements of the Nursing and Midwifery Board of Australia's (NMBA) - English language skills registration standard.

Bachelor of Nursing in Australia: Scholarships

Pursuing Bachelor of Nursing in Australia has many benefits. The universities in Australia offer numerous scholarships that help students manage their finances and ease their burdens. With outstanding academic grades and exceptional English proficiency scores, students can easily get a scholarship in Australia.

Here are the different types of scholarships that are available to international students in Australia:

Merit-Based Scholarships
Faculty and Departmental Scholarships
Accommodation Scholarships

Cost of Studying Bachelor of Nursing in Australia

The cost of studying Bachelor of Nursing program in Australia is different for different universities. Students can consult counselors at Canam, who provide complete study-abroad guidance across India.

FAQ

How many years is a nursing course in Australia?

Regarding the standard study plan, the bachelor of nursing is for three years in Australia, though, with fast-tracking, it can be completed in 2 years. This course equips students with the knowledge, competencies, and skills required to be eligible to apply for registration with AHPRA and the Nursing and Midwifery Board of Australia.

What is the eligibility for Nursing in Australia?

To pursue Nursing in Australia, you must complete your formal schooling and take, IELTS, TOEFL or PTE scores. You must also provide documents such as a resume, statement of purpose, letters of recommendation, etc.

How much does it cost to study Nursing in Australia?

Australia has some top universities where students can pursue a Bachelor of Nursing.

Is Australia good for studying nursing?

Nursing education in Australia is one of the best since it has obvious benefits. Students can apply for a diploma, bachelor’s and master’s nursing degree in Australia. The graduates are offered jobs at various levels based on their qualifications and opportunities for further studies.

Which nursing course is best in Australia?

Here are some of the top nursing courses that students can pursue in Australia:
 
•Bachelor of Nursing (Advanced Studies)
•Bachelor of Midwifery
•Bachelor of Nursing Science
•Master of Advanced Nursing
•Master of Midwifery

Can I study nursing for free in Australia?

It is reported that from 2023 to 2024: Future nurses and midwives undertaking an undergraduate degree in nursing and midwifery will study for free, providing they join a public health service upon completion and stay for two years.
